        "#THE SPARKS FOUNDATION\n",
        "#Task 2 : Prediction using Unsupervised ML\n",
        "###predicting the optimum number of clusters from dataset 'Iris' \n",
        "###and representing it visually.\n",
        "#NAME: Chandu B L"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "4-QFIPQ1O_f8"
      },
      "source": [
        "#Importing the libraries "
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "3oha2OEGNYU_"
      },
      "source": [
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "from sklearn import datasets\n",
        "%matplotlib inline"
      ],
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "9f5iCdSWPP-6"
      },
      "source": [
        "#Loading data set"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "l2GyyokqPGTe",
        "outputId": "bda55831-69fe-43bf-8d1c-820ba46a1b88",
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        }
      },
      "source": [
        "iris = datasets.load_iris()\n",
        "iris_df = pd.DataFrame(iris.data, columns = iris.feature_names)\n",
        "print(iris_df)"
      ],
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "     sepal length (cm)  sepal width (cm)  petal length (cm)  petal width (cm)\n",

            "2                  4.7               3.2                1.3               0.2\n",
            "3                  4.6               3.1                1.5               0.2\n",
            "4                  5.0               3.6                1.4               0.2\n",
            "..                 ...               ...                ...               ...\n",
            "145                6.7               3.0                5.2               2.3\n",
            "146                6.3               2.5                5.0               1.9\n",

            "148                6.2               3.4                5.4               2.3\n",

            "\n",
            "[150 rows x 4 columns]\n"
          ],

        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",

        "outputId": "209bfd40-4bbd-4618-b866-dabf4c8b9a0c",

        }
      },
      "source": [
        "print(iris.target_names)"
      ],
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "['setosa' 'versicolor' 'virginica']\n"
          ],
          "name": "stdout"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "PDZXkx4uUb5o"
      },
      "source": [
        "#Finding the optimum number of clusters for k-means classification"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "3g56imAiQaRO",
        "outputId": "fa2b51e9-5618-44ff-cb64-5cd63a01acd5",
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 295
        }
      },
      "source": [
        "x = iris_df.iloc[:, [0, 1, 2, 3]].values\n",
        "from sklearn.cluster import KMeans\n",
        "wcss = []\n",
        "for i in range(1, 11):\n",
        "    kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters = i, init = 'k-means++', \n",
        "                    max_iter = 300, n_init = 10, random_state = 0)\n",
        "    kmeans.fit(x)\n",
        "    wcss.append(kmeans.inertia_)\n",
        "# Plotting the results onto a line graph,\n",
        "#allowing us to observe 'The elbow'\n",
        "plt.plot(range(1, 11), wcss)\n",
        "plt.title('The elbow method')\n",
        "plt.xlabel('Number of clusters')\n",
        "plt.ylabel('WCSS') # Within cluster sum of squares\n",
        "plt.show()"
      ],
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "display_data",
          "data": {

    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",

      },
      "source": [
        "#Creating the kmeans classifier"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "PmYCHCmuQiMM"
      },
      "source": [
        "x = pd.DataFrame(iris.data, columns=\n",
        "                 ['Sepal Length',\n",
        "                  'Sepal Width', \n",
        "                  'Petal Length',\n",
        "                  'Petal Width'])\n",
        "y = pd.DataFrame(iris.target, columns=['Target'])"
      ],
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "frGi9HdUU5pt"
      },
      "source": [

    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "S1WCqpJLRSAw",
        "outputId": "b104ccae-5632-4965-f873-258f861289f5",
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 400
        }
      },
      "source": [
        "plt.figure(figsize=(15,4))\n",
        "colors = np.array(['red', 'green', 'blue'])\n",
        "iris_targets_legend = np.array(iris.target_names)\n",
        "\n",
        "plt.subplot(1, 2, 1)\n",
        "plt.scatter(x['Sepal Length'], x['Sepal Width'], c=colors[y['Target']])\n",
        "plt.title('Sepal Length vs Sepal Width')\n",
        "print(\"\\nRed represents Setosa\\nGreen represents Versicolor\")\n",
        "print(\"Blue represents Virginica\\n\")\n",
        "\n",
        "plt.subplot(1,2,2)\n",
        "plt.scatter(x['Petal Length'], x['Petal Width'], c= colors[y['Target']])\n",
        "plt.title('Petal Length vs Petal Width')\n",
        "print(\"\\n\")"
